    <string name="guideline_res_title">1. Image Resolution</string>
    <string name="guideline_res_desc">All designs should be at least 300 DPI (dots per inch) to ensure a crisp, high-quality print. Low-resolution images may appear blurry.</string>
    <string name="guideline_formats_title">2. File Formats</string>
    <string name="guideline_formats_desc">We accept high-quality JPEG, PNG, PDF, and TIFF files. PNG is recommended for designs requiring transparency.</string>
    <string name="guideline_bleed_title">3. Bleed Margins</string>
    <string name="guideline_bleed_desc">Please keep a 3mm safety margin (bleed) on all sides. Keep important text and logos at least 5mm away from the edge.</string>
    <string name="guideline_color_title">4. Color Formats</string>
    <string name="guideline_color_desc">Designs should ideally be in CMYK color mode. While we accept RGB, colors may shift slightly during the printing process.</string>

